\begin_layout Definition
A point 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 is a 
\series bold
limit point
\series default
 of a set 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 if every 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon$
\end_inset

-neighborhood 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{\epsilon}(x)$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 intersects the set 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 at some point other than 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Example
\begin_inset Formula $0$
\end_inset

 is a limit point of 
\begin_inset Formula $(0,1)$
\end_inset

