\begin_layout Theorem
(i) The union of a finite collection of closed sets is closed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Theorem
(ii) The intersection of an arbitrary collection of closed sets is closed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Note that these are the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

opposite
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 properties of those satisfied by open sets.
 De Morgan's Laws state that for any collection of sets 
\begin_inset Formula $\{E_{\lambda}:\lambda\in\Lambda\}$
\end_inset

 it is true that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\Big(\bigcup_{\lambda\in\Lambda}E_{\lambda}\Big)^{c}=\bigcap_{\lambda\in\Lambda}E_{\lambda}^{c}\text{ and }\Big(\bigcap_{\lambda\in\Lambda}E_{\lambda}\Big)^{c}=\bigcup_{\lambda\in\Lambda}E_{\lambda}^{c}.
\]

\end_inset

The details are left as Exercise 3.2.9.
\end_layout

